---
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import SpacingStep from '../../components/SpacingStep.astro';

interface SpaceSpec {
  readonly token: string;
  readonly rem: string;
  readonly px: string;
  readonly usage: string;
}

const scale: readonly SpaceSpec[] = [
  { token: '--space-1', rem: '0.25rem', px: '4px', usage: 'Tightest typographic gap — icon-to-label.' },
  { token: '--space-2', rem: '0.5rem', px: '8px', usage: 'Label-to-input, list-item-to-list-item.' },
  { token: '--space-3', rem: '0.75rem', px: '12px', usage: 'Within-component padding for small controls.' },
  { token: '--space-4', rem: '1rem', px: '16px', usage: 'Default stack gap. Component-internal padding.' },
  { token: '--space-5', rem: '1.25rem', px: '20px', usage: 'Card padding, comfortable in-component spacing.' },
  { token: '--space-6', rem: '1.5rem', px: '24px', usage: 'Default <code class="gw-mono">gw-card</code> padding. Page edge padding.' },
  { token: '--space-8', rem: '2rem', px: '32px', usage: 'Section-level gap between unrelated blocks.' },
  { token: '--space-10', rem: '2.5rem', px: '40px', usage: 'Above-H2 spacing inside prose. Major breaks.' },
  { token: '--space-12', rem: '3rem', px: '48px', usage: 'Stack-XL gap. Top-level page-section separation.' },
  { token: '--space-16', rem: '4rem', px: '64px', usage: 'Hero spacing, page-section gaps on wider layouts.' },
  { token: '--space-20', rem: '5rem', px: '80px', usage: 'Reserved for the largest hero or chapter breaks.' },
];
---

<DocsLayout title="Spacing" description="The single scale of spacing tokens that backs every margin, padding, and gap in Groundwork">
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-stack--lg">
      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h1 class="gw-heading-l">Spacing</h1>
        <p>Groundwork uses one spacing scale. Components reference these tokens; designers choose from the same closed set. The scale is non-linear past <code class="gw-mono">--space-6</code> — gaps double rather than continuing in 4px increments — and skips numbers deliberately (there is no <code class="gw-mono">--space-7</code> or <code class="gw-mono">--space-9</code>). Each step is a chosen value, not an oversight.</p>
        <p>Every value is expressed in <code class="gw-mono">rem</code>; pixel equivalents assume the browser's default 16px root font size.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-card">
        <ul class="docs-spacing-scale gw-stack--sm" role="list">
          {scale.map((step) => <SpacingStep token={step.token} rem={step.rem} px={step.px} usage={step.usage} />)}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <section class="gw-stack" aria-labelledby="spacing-usage">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m" id="spacing-usage">Using a spacing token</h2>
        <p class="gw-body--sm">Reach for the layout primitives first — <a class="gw-link" href="/styles/layout/#layout-stack"><code class="gw-mono">gw-stack</code></a> for vertical rhythm and <a class="gw-link" href="/styles/layout/#layout-cluster"><code class="gw-mono">gw-cluster</code></a> for horizontal groups — both of which already pull from this scale. Use raw tokens in component CSS only when the primitives don't fit.</p>
        <CodeBlock>{`.gw-field {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: var(--space-1);
}

.gw-card {
  padding: var(--space-6);
}`}</CodeBlock>
      </section>

      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Guidance</h2>
        <h3 class="gw-heading-s">Pick from the scale, never a custom value</h3>
        <p>If a layout looks like it needs <code class="gw-mono">14px</code>, snap to <code class="gw-mono">--space-3</code> (12px) or <code class="gw-mono">--space-4</code> (16px). Custom values break the visual rhythm and the closed-scale guarantee — a designer cannot trust that all spacings come from the same set.</p>

        <h3 class="gw-heading-s">Use larger steps for layout, smaller for type</h3>
        <p>As a rule of thumb: <code class="gw-mono">--space-1</code> through <code class="gw-mono">--space-3</code> are typographic gaps. <code class="gw-mono">--space-4</code> through <code class="gw-mono">--space-6</code> are component-internal padding. <code class="gw-mono">--space-8</code> and above are layout-level — gaps between sections of a page.</p>

        <h3 class="gw-heading-s">No override utilities yet</h3>
        <p>Groundwork does not ship spacing utility classes — there is no <code class="gw-mono">.gw-margin-top-4</code> or equivalent. Layout responsibilities belong in the template via <code class="gw-mono">gw-stack</code> / <code class="gw-mono">gw-cluster</code>, or inside a component's own CSS. If the absence becomes painful enough, the question is worth re-opening as a system feature.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="gw-prose">
        <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Related</h2>
        <ul class="gw-list">
          <li><a class="gw-link" href="/styles/layout/">Layout</a> — the stack and cluster primitives that consume the spacing scale.</li>
          <li><a class="gw-link" href="/styles/typography/">Typography</a> — line-height tokens that pair with vertical spacing.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .docs-spacing-scale {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
